        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued June 6 at 3:45PM MDT until June 6 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM MDT, A visitor to the Grand Staircase Escalante Visitor
Center reported flash flooding in Big Horn Canyon. This flood wave
will continue to travel downstream within the Harris Wash basin.
Between 0.75 and 1.25 inches of rain have fallen. Flash flooding is
already occurring.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of normally dry washes,
creeks and streams, backcountry roads, and slot canyons.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Harris Wash Basin, Hole-in-the-Rock Road near Bighorn Canyon,
Zebra and Tunnel Slot Canyons.

This includes the following streams and drainages...
Harris Wash and Alvey Wash.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Flooding is occurring or is imminent. It is important to know where
you are relative to streams, rivers, or creeks which can become
killers in heavy rains. Campers and hikers should avoid streams or
creeks.</instruction>
